Program: Outlook
Title: Pressures on Hospital Doctors in Baghdad
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbsft
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Nearly 200 civilians are killed or injured every day in Iraq. A look at the daily pressures for hospital doctors in Baghdad. Also, the young Afghani at university in the US who was illiterate until 8 years ago. Sergei Kotov, the Russian professor who became a king in Ghana. An audio portrait of life in Hyderabad. Interview with Reece and Ross Clarke the ballet dancing brothers from Glasgow. Show less